S4E1.title: The One Where No One Proposes
S4E1.des:
Because of a misunderstanding, Rachel finds
                herself engaged to Joey instead of Ross, who was planning to propose.

S4E2.title: The One Where Emma Cries
S4E2.des:
Somebody ends up in the hospital when Joey
                attempts to apologize to Ross for mistakenly asking Rachel to marry him.

S4E3.title: The One with the Pediatrician
S4E3.des:
Rachel's constant calls to Emma's pediatrician
                force him to reject her as a patient.

S4E4.title: The One with the Sharks
S4E4.des:
Phoebe fears losing Mike, and her self-doubt is
                exacerbated by Ross' foolish comments.

S4E5.title: The One with Phoebe's Birthday Dinner
S4E5.des:
Rachel is afraid to leave Emma with a
                babysitter.

S4E6.title: The One with the Male Nanny
S4E6.des:
Ross jealously mocks Rachel's choice of an
                oversensitive male nanny for Emma.

S4E7.title: The One with Ross' Inappropriate Song
S4E7.des:
When Chandler's former romantic rival decides to
                sell his apartment, Chandler persuades Joey to help him inspect it on the sly.

S4E8.title: The One with Rachel's Other Sister
S4E8.des:
Rachel's self-centered younger sister, Amy,
                ruins everyone's Thanksgiving dinner with her uncensored observations.

S4E9.title: The One with Rachel's Phone Number
S4E9.des:
While on a night out with Phoebe, Rachel
                impulsively gives her telephone number to a handsome restaurant patron.

S4E10.title: The One with Christmas in Tulsa
S4E10.des:
Because of a critical deadline at work, Chandler
                is stuck spending Christmas in Tulsa, Okla.

S4E11.title: The One Where Rachel Goes Back to Work
S4E11.des:
While visiting her workplace to show off baby
                Emma, Rachel is surprised to find a handsome temp who's been doing her job.

S4E12.title: The One with Phoebe's Rats
S4E12.des:
Rachel is irritated to learn that her handsome
                workplace rival has been invited to her birthday party.

S4E13.title: The One Where Monica Sings
S4E13.des:
While Rachel sorts out her conflicted feelings
                for Gavin, Ross sets out to make her jealous, enlisting Chandler to help him meet attractive women.

S4E14.title: The One with the Blind Dates
S4E14.des:
In an attempt to reunite Rachel and Ross, Joey
                and Phoebe arrange awful blind dates for both of them.

S4E15.title: The One with the Mugging
S4E15.des:
Joey develops an unusual acting method to
                impress a famous fellow actor. Meanwhile, Chandler accepts an internship at an advertising agency.

S4E16.title: The One with the Boob Job
S4E16.des:
Phoebe asks Mike to move in with her, but coming
                so close to married life may cause trouble in their relationship.

S4E17.title: The One with the Memorial Service
S4E17.des:
When Chandler jokingly posts an outrageous
                biography about Ross on his college alumni Web site, Ross retaliates.

S4E18.title: The One with the Lottery
S4E18.des:
Hoping to win a huge jackpot, the friends pool
                their money and buy dozens of lottery tickets.

S4E19.title: The One with Rachel's Dream
S4E19.des:
Nervous because his daytime-drama role requires
                him to act as if he's deeply in love with a woman, Joey rehearses with Rachel.

S4E20.title: The One with the Soap Opera Party
S4E20.des:
Ross is excited when he meets fellow
                paleontologist Charlie Wheeler, who's a stunning beauty.

S4E21.title: The One with the Fertility Test
S4E21.des:
Ross is in agony because Charlie is dating Joey.
                Meanwhile, Chandler and Monica visit a fertility clinic.

S4E22.title: The One with the Donor
S4E22.des:
Disappointed to learn that they can't conceive a
                baby naturally, Monica and Chandler consider their options.

S4E23.title: The One in Barbados
S4E23.des:
The gang accompanies Ross to a paleontology
                convention in Barbados, where Ross bonds with Charlie while Joey and Rachel get drunk together.

year:
Rachel finds herself surprisingly adept at taking care
            of Emma but struggles to define her complicated relationships with Joey and Ross.
about:
